cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a supervised learning framework for approximating a model predictive controller (MPC) for a wide class of nonlinear systems. The use of neural networks as a standard supervised learning technique suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. However, the focus on control and stability suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The use of statistical learning bounds and Hoeffding’s Inequality suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The application of the proposed framework to a nonlinear benchmark problem suggests that it could belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for control suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
